SolarCalc_Leading: This is a web service for calculating the position of the sun in the sky, at any point you specify on the globe.
SolarCalc_Body: For a known date and time, you can calculate the height of the Sun above the horizon and its azimuth. By the position of the Sun, the direction and length of the shadow are calculated. So you can determine the shading from buildings at your grounds. If you put Sun’s altitude or azimuth, then you will be able to perform the inverse calculation: get the time when the Sun appears in this position. For clarity, you can see the animation of the trajectory of the Sun during the day and year. Use the SUN CALCULATOR and remember: SOL LUCET OMNIBUS!

MigratedAway_Body:
As we care about user experience and service sustainability, we had to partition IRRISketch servers for different geographics. All your user data is stored safely on protected servers. Now you just have to switch to another domain zone, by clicking the button below.
Sorry for inconvenience!

P.S. if you think there is a mistake, and your account shouldn't have been moved, please inform us about it via email mail@irrisketch.com

tool_Obstacle_examples: Anything that affects sprinklers disposition + PREVENTS THE WATER JET from reaching the desired area. For example, small architectural forms, a wall, a tree, a tall bush, etc.
tool_PlacementObstacle_examples: Anything that affects sprinklers disposition + DOES NOT PREVENT THE WATER JET from reaching the desired area. For example, a path, a low flowerbed, a small bush, a stone composition on a lawn etc.
